) is already familiar with the newer technology, owing to the university courses/ social media/ gadgets. But it is the ageing population for whom the struggle is getting real. The technologies popular in the last decade seem to be fading away and  there is need to constantly keep updating, evolving and learning to adapt to this Digitally Transformed World!

Cloud Computing, Machine Learning,  Big Data and BI seem to be the new pillars for Digital Transformation, and more and more people are planning to invest time and money in learning these in the next 2 years.

